.TH COOKIE-MONSTER 1 "February 2026" "cookie-monster-cli 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cookie-monster \- capture browser auth headers from Chrome DevTools and replay requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cookie-monster
[\-\-version]
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cookie-monster
captures request headers from a Chrome DevTools network stream and can replay HTTP requests using captured auth/session headers.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B capture
Capture request headers from Chrome.
.TP
.B replay
Replay an HTTP request with captured headers.
.SH CAPTURE OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-chrome-host
DevTools host (default: 127.0.0.1).
.TP
.B \-\-chrome-port
DevTools port (default: 9222).
.TP
.B \-\-browser
Browser to launch when using \fB\-\-launch-chrome\fR (\fBchrome\fR or \fBedge\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-duration
Capture duration in seconds.
.TP
.B \-\-max-records
Maximum number of captured requests.
.TP
.B \-\-target-hint
Substring to match tab/request URLs.
.TP
.B \-\-output
Capture output JSONL file.
.TP
.B \-\-header
Repeatable header allowlist item.
.TP
.B \-\-include-all-headers
Store all request headers.
.TP
.B \-\-launch-browser
Launch browser before capture.
.TP
.B \-\-launch-chrome
Deprecated alias for \fB\-\-launch-browser\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-browser-path
Path to browser executable.
.TP
.B \-\-chrome-path
Deprecated alias for \fB\-\-browser-path\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-user-data-dir
Chrome user data dir root.
.TP
.B \-\-profile-directory
Chrome profile folder (for example: Default, Profile 1).
.TP
.B \-\-open-url
URL to open when launching Chrome.
.TP
.B \-\-headless
Run launched Chrome in headless mode.
.TP
.B \-\-keep-open
Do not terminate launched Chrome after capture.
.SH REPLAY OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-capture-file
Capture JSONL input file.
.TP
.B \-\-request-url
Target URL to request.
.TP
.B \-\-method
HTTP method (default: GET).
.TP
.B \-\-url-contains
Filter capture records by URL substring.
.TP
.B \-\-timeout
Request timeout in seconds.
.TP
.B \-\-output
Write response JSON to file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
cookie-monster capture --launch-chrome \\
  --user-data-dir "/Users/me/Library/Application Support/Google/Chrome" \\
  --profile-directory Default \\
  --open-url "https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/<id>" \\
  --target-hint supabase.com --duration 30 --include-all-headers

cookie-monster replay --capture-file captures.jsonl \\
  --method GET --url-contains supabase.com \\
  --request-url "https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/<id>"
.fi
.SH MANUAL VIEW
Use:
.PP
.B man ./man/cookie-monster.1
.SH SECURITY
Use only on accounts/systems you are authorized to access.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation in README.md.
